  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Initiating Data Extraction**\n\nI\'m now focused on the initial parsing of the video data. My goal is to extract the key components: shots, characters, and narrative structure. I\'m building a framework to process the video and start identifying distinct shots, their timing, and visual elements like camera movement and composition. I\'m also planning to recognize and log key characters within the scene.\n\n\n**Refining Project Scope**\n\nI\'m now shifting gears. The initial video data analysis is taking a backseat as I hone in on the core task: building the React web app. I\'ve got a clearer picture: the app will display the video analysis (in JSON format, as specified), and incorporate the \"High Density\" design theme. I\'m already envisioning the components and their interactions, focused on a sleek, data-rich user interface.\n\n\n**Investigating Server-Side Capabilities**\n\nI\'m digging into the project structure. I was hoping for server-side capabilities, and initially, `package.json` and `tsconfig.json` showed the presence of `express`. However, after examining the file directory, a dedicated `server.ts` file is missing. This raises questions: should the video analysis be client-side? Or, would it be better to pre-process the video and hardcode the results? The Gemini API use makes this more complex.\n\n\n**Considering Data Delivery**\n\nI\'m now contemplating how to handle the video analysis data. Should I hardcode the data into the app for the specific airship video the user uploaded, or should the data be generated dynamically? I\'m processing the video, identifying the characters and scenes. The video features a short-haired girl with a black cape, a professor with glasses, and a burly man. They jump from the airship, slide down a snowy mountain, swim underwater, run through a candy land, and battle monsters in a desert. I\'m focusing on key characters: the girl\'s magical powers stand out.\n\n\n**Analyzing Character Dynamics**\n\nI\'m now diving into character interactions and the overall narrative structure, based on the video\'s unfolding events. The scene is set with an arguing professor and burly man inside a steampunk airship. The professor is a contrast to the burly, crude, and rowdy man. There is also a young girl. My focus is now on the unfolding story. I\'m noting the professor\'s calculations, in contrast to the burly man\'s crude behavior.\n\n\n**Mapping Narrative Beats**\n\nI\'m now mapping the video\'s climax and resolution. I see the characters facing alien-like monsters in ancient desert ruins with obelisks. The girl utilizes a magical weapon, while the professor and burly man fight with a revolver and hammer, respectively. The ending shows them defeating the monsters and approaching a desert portal, continuing their character dynamic. I\'m focusing on incorporating these detailed events into the analysis.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 10
      nanos: 377388246
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
