  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Addressing Asset Import Errors**\n\nI\'ve hit a snag with importing image files (JPG/PNG) directly into TypeScript. Without a declaration file (`d.ts`), the compiler throws \"Cannot find module...\" errors. It seems the asset declarations are missing. Now, I must find a solution.\n\n\n**Refining Import Strategy**\n\nI\'ve realized static ESM imports for images are unnecessary. Referencing image paths as absolute string literals (e.g., `/src/assets/...`) is cleaner and more robust. This bypasses TypeScript asset declarations entirely. I\'m now updating `/src/data.ts` to reflect this change, which will simplify the code.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
